  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-08-02",
    "date": "2023-05-04T10:28:38Z",
    "text": "Law Enforcement De-Escalation Training Act of 2022\n\nThis bill directs the Department of Justice (DOJ) to develop scenario-based training curricula (or identify existing curricula) that includes topics such as alternatives to the use of force, de-escalation tactics, and safely responding to an individual experiencing a mental, behavioral health, or suicidal crisis.\n\nThe bill also directs DOJ to make grants to states for costs associated with providing the training to law enforcement officers or mental health professionals."
  },
